Daily Post reports that a heavy storm that accompanied the early rains of the year in Ondo State has wreaked havoc in Irese community, Ifedore Local Government Area of state,The rainstorm, which occurred on Friday night, destroyed several houses, including the community’s health centre, city hall, and schools, among others, leaving the majority of citizens homeless.  It also wreaked havoc on a church and a poultry farm in the town, causing damage worth millions of naira.Following the incident, the residents lamented the storm’s devastating impact on them and their livelihood.  Source Rainstorm Renders Many Homeless In Kebbi In "News" By George Edomwonyi Auchi - The Auchi Magistrate’s Court 1 building in Auchi, headquarters of the Etsako-West Local Government Area of Edo has collapsed following a heavy rainstorm on Wednesday. A Correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) who visited the court on Thursday reports that the rainstorm also… In "News" The Nation reports that a 14- year- old boy identified as Faith Utobo died on Thursday evening when a church building collapsed after a heavy rain storm. The rainstorm was said to have wreck havoc at Olu foam, Omoniyi Estate and Igoba areas of Akure, the Ondo State capital. Six… In "Metro"